Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course

Class Activity

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course.Activity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Conflict
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Course
    public abstract class Activity
extends java.lang.Object
implements Conflict
    This class consist of methods used to generate and interact with the activity method. It will be used to get and set the title, meeting days, start time and end time of events. It has 1 child class, Course

      • setActivityTime

        public void setActivityTime​(int startTime,
                            int endTime)
        Sets the start time and end time of the course. It will throw an IllegalArgumentException if the hour is not between 0 and 23, the minute is not between 0 and 59, if the time format is wrong, or if the meeting days is set to A. Will return if called with meetingDays are A and both start and end times are 0
        Parameters:
        startTime - course start time
        endTime - course end time time are both 0
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when there is a time listed (beside 0) when meeting days is 'A'
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the end time is before the start time
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the time format is wrong (not 3 or 4 digits)
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the 'hours' field is not between 0 and 23 (inclusive)
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the 'minute' field is not between 0 and 59 (inclusive)

      • getMeetingString

        public java.lang.String getMeetingString()
        Returns a string of the meeting days with the time with it in the format of [days] [starttime]-[endtime] with am/pm attached. If meeting days is A, then the string will read Arranged
        Returns:
        either the meeting days with time, or "Arranged" if A

      • checkConflict

        public void checkConflict​(Activity possibleConflictingActivity)
                   throws ConflictException
        Compare this.object to another object to see if they have conflicting days unless they are arranged. If they do, the start and end times are then compared to confirm that there is no overlap in start or end times
        Specified by:
        checkConflict in interface Conflict
        Parameters:
        possibleConflictingActivity - the activity being compared to this.object
        Throws:
        ConflictException - when 'this' start time is after possibleConflictingActivity start time while before possibleConflictingActivity end time
        ConflictException - when 'this' end time is after possibleConflictingActivity start time while before possibleConflictingActivity end time
        ConflictException - when 'this' start time is before possibleConflictingActivity start time while 'this' end time is after possibleConflictingActivity end time
